            <div style="font-family:'GT Flexa Extended','GT Flexa','Barlow Condensed','Oswald',sans-serif;font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:#00A1C4;letter-spacing:0.18em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:20px;"></div>

            <div style="font-family:'Aktiv Grotesk','aktiv-grotesk','Helvetica Neue','Arial',sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:400;color:#1E293B;margin-bottom:16px;line-height:1.6;text-align:justify;">Dear Investor,</div>

            <div style="font-family:'Aktiv Grotesk','aktiv-grotesk','Helvetica Neue','Arial',sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;line-height:1.75;text-align:justify;margin-bottom:14px;">Taranis Market Sentiment ended the month of April 2026 with a net performance of +34.1%.</div>

            <div style="font-family:'Aktiv Grotesk','aktiv-grotesk','Helvetica Neue','Arial',sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:300;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;text-align:justify;margin-bottom:14px;">In spite of geopolitical uncertainties, the market rebounded strongly in <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">April</span>, particularly in the <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">technology sector</span>. Our systematic strategy contributed substantially to performance, accounting for approximately two-thirds of the fund's total return. <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">The S&P 500 rose around 10%, a move that many characterize as an outlier. This was the second-best April on record</span>. A monthly gain above <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">10%</span> has occurred only 13 times in the past 50 years, and only four times since 1996. It was also the strongest month for the index since 2020. TMS managed to benefit from it.</div>

            <div style="font-family:'Aktiv Grotesk','aktiv-grotesk','Helvetica Neue','Arial',sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;line-height:1.75;text-align:justify;margin-bottom:14px;"><span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">While the market went up</span>, the AAII <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">bull-bear indicator</span> remained low until the third week of April. Bearishness was particularly pronounced during this period, with the VIX starting above 25 and finishing the month below 16.</div>

            <div style="font-family:'Aktiv Grotesk','aktiv-grotesk','Helvetica Neue','Arial',sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:300;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;text-align:justify;margin-bottom:28px;">Our long/short strategy, which focuses on innovation and disruption and serves as a continuation of the <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">systematic strategy</span> but using different instruments, <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">contributed about one-third of the fund's performance</span>. This was achieved despite a much smaller allocation (<span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">$23M</span> gross and <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">60%</span> of AUM). <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">The strategy is now up 47.5%</span> since inception and <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">42.2% YTD</span>. We positioned it with a growth bias in a market environment that we view as highly favorable for highly disruptive names. Accordingly, we selected top-quality companies in innovative sectors identified through our top-down systematic process.</div>

            <div style="font-family:'Aktiv Grotesk','aktiv-grotesk','Helvetica Neue','Arial',sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:300;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;text-align:justify;">
